  "text": "Information integration is based on semantic interoperability that emphasizes the importance of the information and focuses on enabling content, data, and information to interoperate with software systems outside their origin [CITATION_1] . The aim of semantic interoperability is to provide the ability to bridge semantic conflicts arising from differences in implicit meanings, perspectives, and assumptions for co-operating enterprises, thus creating a semantically compatible information environment based on the agreed concepts between different business entities [CITATION_2] . The basis for ontology-driven knowledge management was formed in EU projects On-To-Knowledge (On-To-Knowledge, 2008) and continued in Semantic Knowledge Technologies (SEKT) (SEKT, 2008) that researched the development and exploitation of semantic knowledge technologies.",
